    "\", p.38-39 27 Zutshi, Grilo [110] Deposits & loans Insurance \"During 2020, the Ethereum Blockchain has seen the development and adoption of several decentralized finance apps which automate financial functions such as lending, borrowing, insurance all through tokens and smart contracts without requiring central intermediaries.",
    "\", p.3 No Author(s) Risks Text passage 1 Caldarelli and Ellul [17] Flawed oracle (Front Running)\"Front-running attacks are due to the natural condition in which the oracle is the first to be aware of critical data uploaded to the blockchain to run a smart contract.",
    "\", p.15 1 Caldarelli and Ellul [17] Flawed oracle (Sybil attacks)\"Sybil attacks are means to manipulate decentralized oracle platforms.",
    "To obtain the majority of votes, the Sybil replicates its vote to gain a higher weight when compared to others.",
    "\", p.16 1 Caldarelli and Ellul [17] Flawed oracle (Selection bias)\"Selection bias refers to the situation in which a DeFi service selects a data source that is not explicitly meant to serve as an oracle."
